as conducted for TDI handling, storage, and process. The PHA used What-if/Checklist methodology and included participants from operations, maintenances, and Environmental Health and Safety (EH&S) management at the facility.  A copy of the PHA is available at the facility and the findings have been communicated to the appropriate facility personnel.



The facility takes responsibility for safe operations seriously and has developed a robust process safety management (PSM) program for toxics and flammable substances handled and processed in the facility.  This prevention program is applicable to TDI also.  Specifically for TDI, the prevention programs elements include:



?       Detailed process safety information (PSI) for all areas where TDI is handled, stored, or used;

?       Process hazard analysis (PHA) for all areas where TDI is handled, stored, or used;

?       Safe operating procedures for handling, storage and movement of TDI within building;

?       Mechanical integrity program including preventive maintenance for TDI handling equipment;

?       Incident reporting and investigation program for the facility;

?       Pre-startup safety review program;

?       Management of change program;

?       Emergency response plan for the facility;

?       Training to operators handling TDI;

?       Contractor safety program;

?       Hot work permit program; and

?       Inspection and audit program

Other general safety programs at the facility includes:

?       Safety data sheets for all flammable and toxic substances available at locations accessible to the facility operators;

?       Emergency showers and spill prevention kits are available throughout Building 1;

?       Forklift operators are trained on safe handling of loads;

?       Fume extraction systems are used during operations in the reactors;

?       Sprinkler system is available throughout Building 1 at strategic locations;

